<h1>Connekt — Detailed User & Technical Guide</h1>

<p>This document explains how to navigate and operate the Connekt application.</p>

<h2>Table of Contents</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Quick Start</li>
  <li>Top-level Navigation &amp; UI</li>
  <li>Primary User Flows (Applicants, Recruiters)</li>
  <li>Admin &amp; Moderation</li>
  <li>Data Model &amp; APIs</li>
  <li>Localization &amp; Theme</li>
  <li>Environment &amp; Deployment</li>
  <li>Troubleshooting</li>
</ol>

<h2>1. Quick Start</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Install dependencies: <code>npm install</code></li>
  <li>Create a <code>.env.local</code> with required Supabase keys and <code>NEXTAUTH_URL</code>.</li>
  <li>Apply database schema in <code>supabase_schema.sql</code> to your Supabase project.</li>
  <li>Run locally: <code>npm run dev</code> and open <a href="http://localhost:3000">http://localhost:3000</a>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Top-level Navigation &amp; UI</h2>
<p>The main app navigation is implemented in <code>src/components/Navigation.tsx</code>. Key UI pieces you will use:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Header / Navigation:</strong> Links to Home, Jobs, Listings, Post, Dashboard, Profile, and Admin (if authorized). Mobile menu collapses into a drawer.</li>
  <li><strong>Locale Switcher:</strong> Provided by <code>src/components/LocaleSwitcher.tsx</code>. Switches between English/French and reloads localized routes (URL prefix <code>/en</code> or <code>/fr</code>).</li>
  <li><strong>Theme Toggle:</strong> <code>src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx</code> toggles dark/light mode; preferences are stored in localStorage.</li>
  <li><strong>Splash/Loader:</strong> App-level loader in <code>src/components/SplashLoader.tsx</code> handles initial fetches.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Navigation behavior</h3>
<p>Routes are localized under <code>src/app/[locale]</code>. When navigating, the app loads route-specific translation JSON from <code>src/messages</code> and renders server-side where possible using Next.js App Router patterns.</p>

<h2>3. Primary User Flows</h2>

<h3>Applicant (Student)</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Sign up / sign in via the Auth page. Auth is handled by Supabase (see <code>src/lib/supabase.ts</code>).</li>
  <li>Complete your profile at <code>/[locale]/profile</code>. Profile includes headline, skills, experience, education, and a resume link.</li>
  <li>Browse jobs at <code>/[locale]/jobs</code>. Use filters, search, and sort. Click a job for details (<code>/[locale]/jobs/[jobId]</code>).</li>
  <li>Click <em>Apply</em> on a job detail to open the application form. Attach a resume (PDF recommended) and submit. Applications are written to the <code>applications</code> table.</li>
  <li>Track your submissions at <code>/[locale]/applications</code>. Status updates appear here (pending/accepted/rejected).</li>
</ol>

<h3>Recruiter / Employer</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Sign in with recruiter credentials. If not yet a recruiter, request elevated access via your admin panel or create an account provisioned for recruiters.</li>
  <li>Post a job via <code>/[locale]/post</code>. Provide title, description, location, tags, application deadline, and optional screening questions.</li>
  <li>Manage postings under <code>/[locale]/listings</code> or <code>/[locale]/jobs</code>. Edit, pause, or remove listings.</li>
  <li>View applicants for each job at <code>/[locale]/applicants/[jobId]</code>. Filter, add private notes, and change application status.</li>
</ol>

<h2>4. Admin &amp; Moderation</h2>
<p>Admin pages are inside <code>src/app/[locale]/admin</code>. Typical admin responsibilities include:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Approving / rejecting job postings in <strong>Job Moderation</strong>.</li>
  <li>Reviewing and bulk-managing applications via <strong>Applications Oversight</strong>.</li>
  <li>User Management: deactivate/reactivate accounts, change roles, and investigate suspicious activity.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How admin auth works</h3>
<p>Server-side admin checks are implemented in <code>src/lib/adminAuth.ts</code>. API route handlers under <code>src/app/api/admin</code> validate requests with server-side credentials or role flags stored in the database. Never expose <code>SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY</code> to the client.</p>

<h2>5. Data Model &amp; APIs</h2>
<p>Core tables (see <code>supabase_schema.sql</code>):</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>profiles</code> — user profile metadata mapped to auth users.</li>
  <li><code>jobs</code> — job postings, with fields for title, description, owner, status, tags, location, and deadline.</li>
  <li><code>applications</code> — submitted applications referencing jobId and profileId, plus status and notes.</li>
</ul>

<h3>API route patterns</h3>
<p>Server handlers live under <code>src/app/api</code>. Admin APIs are under <code>src/app/api/admin</code>. Use server-side fetches for admin data to keep the service role key private.</p>

<h4>Example: fetching applications server-side</h4>
<pre><code>import { createAdminClient } from '@/lib/supabase-admin'

export async function GET(request) {
  const supabase = createAdminClient()
  const { data, error } = await supabase.from('applications').select('*')
  if (error) return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: error.message }), { status: 500 })
  return new Response(JSON.stringify(data), { status: 200 })
}
</code></pre>

<h2>6. Localization &amp; Theme</h2>
<p>Localization files are kept in <code>src/messages</code> grouped per route. To add a locale:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Add the locale folder under <code>src/app</code> (e.g., <code>/es</code>).</li>
  <li>Add translation JSON files under the appropriate messages folders.</li>
  <li>Update navigation in <code>src/i18n/navigation.ts</code> if you add new localized pages.</li>
</ol>

<h2>7. Environment &amp; Deployment</h2>
<p>Required variables (example):</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL</code></li>
  <li><code>NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY</code></li>
  <li><code>SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY</code> (server-only)</li>
  <li><code>NEXTAUTH_URL</code></li>
</ul>

<p>Deploy on Vercel for automatic Next.js optimizations; set the environment variables in your Vercel project settings.</p>

<h2>8. Troubleshooting</h2>
<h3>Common issues</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Blank pages / build errors:</strong> Run <code>npm run build</code> locally to surface compile errors.</li>
  <li><strong>Auth failures:</strong> Confirm Supabase keys and <code>NEXTAUTH_URL</code> match your deployed domain.</li>
  <li><strong>Missing translations:</strong> Ensure JSON keys exist under <code>src/messages</code> for the current route.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Logs &amp; diagnostics</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Server logs are visible in your terminal when running <code>npm run dev</code> or in Vercel/hosting logs for production.</li>
  <li>Supabase provides Auth and Database logs via the Supabase dashboard.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Appendix — File map with responsibilities</h2>
<ul>
  <li><code>src/app/[locale]/auth/page.tsx</code> — Sign-in &amp; sign-up flows</li>
  <li><code>src/app/[locale]/jobs/page.tsx</code> — Job board listing</li>
  <li><code>src/app/[locale]/jobs/[jobId]/page.tsx</code> — Job details and apply action</li>
  <li><code>src/components/Navigation.tsx</code> — Header and primary links</li>
  <li><code>src/lib/supabase.ts</code> — Client-side Supabase</li>
  <li><code>src/lib/supabase-admin.ts</code> — Server-side admin Supabase client</li>
</ul>

<p>End of guide.</p>

</body>
</html>
